{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"Vlru1TrIpjjC4viiNvcMa","title":"Overview","desc":"","updated":1640612898604,"created":1640097191507,"nav_order":1,"custom":{"nav_order":1},"fname":"programming.network.intro","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"662adf07c565a7a80a09fb1977570471","links":[],"anchors":{"intro":{"type":"header","text":"Intro","value":"intro","line":8,"column":0,"depth":1},"network-topologies":{"type":"header","text":"Network Topologies","value":"network-topologies","line":12,"column":0,"depth":1},"point-to-point":{"type":"header","text":"Point to Point","value":"point-to-point","line":16,"column":0,"depth":3},"daisy-chain":{"type":"header","text":"Daisy Chain","value":"daisy-chain","line":20,"column":0,"depth":3},"bus":{"type":"header","text":"Bus","value":"bus","line":26,"column":0,"depth":3},"ring":{"type":"header","text":"Ring","value":"ring","line":32,"column":0,"depth":3},"star":{"type":"header","text":"Star","value":"star","line":40,"column":0,"depth":3},"mesh":{"type":"header","text":"Mesh","value":"mesh","line":50,"column":0,"depth":3},"hybrid":{"type":"header","text":"Hybrid","value":"hybrid","line":54,"column":0,"depth":3},"open-systems-interconnection-reference-model":{"type":"header","text":"Open Systems Interconnection Reference Model","value":"open-systems-interconnection-reference-model","line":59,"column":0,"depth":1},"layer-7---application":{"type":"header","text":"Layer 7 - Application","value":"layer-7---application","line":67,"column":0,"depth":2},"layer-6---presentation":{"type":"header","text":"Layer 6 - Presentation","value":"layer-6---presentation","line":73,"column":0,"depth":2},"layer-5---session":{"type":"header","text":"Layer 5 - Session","value":"layer-5---session","line":79,"column":0,"depth":2},"layer-4---transport":{"type":"header","text":"Layer 4 - Transport","value":"layer-4---transport","line":85,"column":0,"depth":2},"layer-3---network":{"type":"header","text":"Layer 3 - Network","value":"layer-3---network","line":91,"column":0,"depth":2},"layer-2---data-link":{"type":"header","text":"Layer 2 - Data Link","value":"layer-2---data-link","line":97,"column":0,"depth":2},"layer-1---physical":{"type":"header","text":"Layer 1 - Physical","value":"layer-1---physical","line":103,"column":0,"depth":2},"sending-traffic-by-using-data-encapsulation":{"type":"header","text":"Sending Traffic by Using Data Encapsulation","value":"sending-traffic-by-using-data-encapsulation","line":109,"column":0,"depth":1},"tcpip-model":{"type":"header","text":"TCP/IP Model","value":"tcpip-model","line":119,"column":0,"depth":1},"application-layer":{"type":"header","text":"Application Layer","value":"application-layer","line":125,"column":0,"depth":2},"transport-layer":{"type":"header","text":"Transport Layer","value":"transport-layer","line":135,"column":0,"depth":2},"internet-layer":{"type":"header","text":"Internet Layer","value":"internet-layer","line":143,"column":0,"depth":2},"link-layer":{"type":"header","text":"Link Layer","value":"link-layer","line":151,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":[],"parent":"t5w4acej37neksi1gifrvfo","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"overview\">Overview<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#overview\"></a></h1>\n<h1 id=\"intro\">Intro<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#intro\"></a></h1>\n<p><strong>Computer Network</strong> : Connection between two or more devices/nodes that allow each node to share data</p>\n<h1 id=\"network-topologies\">Network Topologies<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#network-topologies\"></a></h1>\n<p><strong>Topology</strong> : Organization of nodes in a network</p>\n<h3 id=\"point-to-point\">Point to Point<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#point-to-point\"></a></h3>\n<p><img src=\"/assets/images/2021-12-22-06-51-39.png\"></p>\n<h3 id=\"daisy-chain\">Daisy Chain<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#daisy-chain\"></a></h3>\n<p><strong>Hop</strong>: Intermediate Node between source and destination node</p>\n<p><img src=\"/assets/images/2021-12-22-06-52-01.png\"></p>\n<h3 id=\"bus\">Bus<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#bus\"></a></h3>\n<p><img src=\"/assets/images/2021-12-22-06-55-34.png\"></p>\n<p>Most common in wireless networks</p>\n<h3 id=\"ring\">Ring<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#ring\"></a></h3>\n<p><img src=\"/assets/images/2021-12-22-06-58-10.png\"></p>\n<p>Traffic travels in a single direction</p>\n<p>Speed can be limited by slowest node in the network</p>\n<h3 id=\"star\">Star<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#star\"></a></h3>\n<p><img src=\"/assets/images/2021-12-22-07-21-27.png\"></p>\n<p>Most common in wireless networks</p>\n<p>Central node is mostly a network switch</p>\n<p>Data can traverse on a single hop</p>\n<h3 id=\"mesh\">Mesh<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#mesh\"></a></h3>\n<p><img src=\"/assets/images/2021-12-22-07-27-34.png\"></p>\n<h3 id=\"hybrid\">Hybrid<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#hybrid\"></a></h3>\n<p><img src=\"/assets/images/2021-12-22-07-30-29.png\"></p>\n<h1 id=\"open-systems-interconnection-reference-model\">Open Systems Interconnection Reference Model<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#open-systems-interconnection-reference-model\"></a></h1>\n<p>OSI Model standardizes networking</p>\n<p><strong>Protocols</strong>: Rules and procedures that determine the format and order of data sent over a network</p>\n<p><img src=\"/assets/images/2021-12-22-20-11-06.png\"></p>\n<h2 id=\"layer-7---application\">Layer 7 - Application<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#layer-7---application\"></a></h2>\n<p>Responsible for identifying hosts and retrieving resources</p>\n<p>e.g. Browsers, Torrent Client</p>\n<h2 id=\"layer-6---presentation\">Layer 6 - Presentation<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#layer-6---presentation\"></a></h2>\n<p>Prepares data for the network layer when data moves down the stack and for application layer when data moves up the stack</p>\n<p>Functions: Encryption/Decryption Encoding</p>\n<h2 id=\"layer-5---session\">Layer 5 - Session<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#layer-5---session\"></a></h2>\n<p>Manages connection lifecycle between nodes on a network</p>\n<p>Functions: Connection establishment, managing connection timeouts, coordinating the mode of operation and connection termination</p>\n<h2 id=\"layer-4---transport\">Layer 4 - Transport<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#layer-4---transport\"></a></h2>\n<p>Controls and coordinates transfer of data between nodes while maintaining the reliability</p>\n<p>Functions: Correcting errors, speed control, chunking data, ack-ing received data</p>\n<h2 id=\"layer-3---network\">Layer 3 - Network<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#layer-3---network\"></a></h2>\n<p>Transmits data between nodes without having a direct point to point connection to the remote node</p>\n<p>Functions: Network management protocols for routing, addressing, multicasting and traffic control</p>\n<h2 id=\"layer-2---data-link\">Layer 2 - Data Link<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#layer-2---data-link\"></a></h2>\n<p>Handles data transfers between two directly connected nodes</p>\n<p>Function: Error detection and Error Correction</p>\n<h2 id=\"layer-1---physical\">Layer 1 - Physical<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#layer-1---physical\"></a></h2>\n<p>Converts bits from the network stack to the physical medium</p>\n<p>Controls bit rate</p>\n<h1 id=\"sending-traffic-by-using-data-encapsulation\">Sending Traffic by Using Data Encapsulation<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#sending-traffic-by-using-data-encapsulation\"></a></h1>\n<p><strong>Payload</strong>: Data travelling down the stack</p>\n<p><strong>Horizontal Communication</strong>: Communication between client and server on the same layer</p>\n<p><img src=\"/assets/images/2021-12-22-21-08-28.png\"></p>\n<p><img src=\"/assets/images/2021-12-22-21-09-23.png\"></p>\n<h1 id=\"tcpip-model\">TCP/IP Model<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#tcpip-model\"></a></h1>\n<p><strong>End-to-End Principle</strong>: Each network segment includes only enough functionality to properly transmit and route bits; all other functionality belongs to the endpoints.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/assets/images/2021-12-22-21-30-48.png\"></p>\n<h2 id=\"application-layer\">Application Layer<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#application-layer\"></a></h2>\n<p>Interacts directly with software applications</p>\n<p>Encompasses three OSI layers</p>\n<p>Protocols: FTP, HTTP, SMTP</p>\n<p>Function: DHCP, DNS</p>\n<h2 id=\"transport-layer\">Transport Layer<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#transport-layer\"></a></h2>\n<p>Handles transfer of data between two node</p>\n<p>Ensures data integrity</p>\n<p>Protocols: TCP, UDP</p>\n<h2 id=\"internet-layer\">Internet Layer<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#internet-layer\"></a></h2>\n<p>Responsible for routing packets of data</p>\n<p>Protocols: IPv4, IPv6, BGP, ICMP, IGMP, IPsec</p>\n<p>Function: Data Delivery</p>\n<h2 id=\"link-layer\">Link Layer<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#link-layer\"></a></h2>\n<p>ARP Translates nodes IP address to MAC address of network interface</p>","noteIndex":{"id":"root","title":"BrainMatter","desc":"","updated":1668313955403,"created":1602915435296,"stub":false,"nav_order":0,"custom":{"stub":false,"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type